Uses of Class
se.kodapan.geojson.GeoJSONGeometry

  • Packages that use GeoJSONGeometry 
    Package Description
    se.kodapan.geojson  

    • Uses of GeoJSONGeometry in se.kodapan.geojson

      Subclasses of GeoJSONGeometry in se.kodapan.geojson 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  GeometryCollection
      Each element in the geometries array of a GeometryCollection is one of the geometry objects described above: { "type": "GeometryCollection", "geometries": [ { "type": "Point", "coordinates": [100.0, 0.0] }, { "type": "LineString", "coordinates": [ [101.0, 0.0], [102.0, 1.0] ] } ] }
      class  LineString
      Coordinates of LineString are an array of positions (see 2.1.1.
      class  MultiLineString
      Coordinates of a MultiLineString are an array of LineString coordinate arrays: { "type": "MultiLineString", "coordinates": [ [ [100.0, 0.0], [101.0, 1.0] ], [ [102.0, 2.0], [103.0, 3.0] ] ] }
      class  MultiPoint
      Coordinates of a MultiPoint are an array of positions: { "type": "MultiPoint", "coordinates": [ [100.0, 0.0], [101.0, 1.0] ] }
      class  MultiPolygon
      Coordinates of a MultiPolygon are an array of Polygon coordinate arrays: { "type": "MultiPolygon", "coordinates": [ [[[102.0, 2.0], [103.0, 2.0], [103.0, 3.0], [102.0, 3.0], [102.0, 2.0]]], [[[100.0, 0.0], [101.0, 0.0], [101.0, 1.0], [100.0, 1.0], [100.0, 0.0]], [[100.2, 0.2], [100.8, 0.2], [100.8, 0.8], [100.2, 0.8], [100.2, 0.2]]] ] }
      class  Point
      Point coordinates are in x, y order (easting, northing for projected coordinates, longitude, latitude for geographic coordinates): { "type": "Point", "coordinates": [100.0, 0.0] }
      class  Polygon
      Coordinates of a Polygon are an array of LinearRing coordinate arrays.
